</span>iv.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Local Model Deployment: If selected
<span class=GramE>in</span> the website, download and deploy selected Local
Models per Schedule D, including quantization optimization for Client Hardware
specifications.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(d)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Account Creation</span></b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;
mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'>:</span> Create Client Account
using Client-provided username and a password that will be accessible to the
client on their dashboard on <span class=SpellE>MonoClaw’s</span> <span
class=GramE>website;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(e)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Logout Protocol</span></b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;
mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'>:</span> Complete logout of all
<span class=SpellE>Sentimento</span> credentials, remove <span class=SpellE>Sentimento</span>
Apple ID from device and remove all <span class=SpellE>Sentimento’s</span> internal
configuration and testing <span class=GramE>software;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(f)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Diagnostic Testing</span></b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;
mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'>:</span> Run hardware and
software diagnostics (logs transmitted to <span class=SpellE>Supabase</span>
per Schedule C<span class=GramE>);</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(g)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Sealing</span></b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;
mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'>:</span> Apply unique numbered <span
class=SpellE>Sentimento</span> Seal to tamper-evident packaging; photograph
seal application; and prepare for shipment.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(h)
<b>Model Verification</b>: For each deployed Local Model, log checksum/hash
verification and <span class=SpellE>licence</span> attribution file (where
required by upstream <span class=SpellE>licence</span>) to <span class=SpellE>Supabase</span>
for compliance <span class=GramE>records;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'>4.2
Password Security and DPA</span></b><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(a)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Generation</span></b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;
mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'>:</span> Initial passwords
generated using cryptographically secure random number generators (NIST SP
800-90A compliant).<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(b)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Transmission</span></b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;
mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'>:</span> Passwords transmitted
to Client via the dashboard of <span class=SpellE>MonoClaw</span> (through
personal client portal accessible after Google SSO).<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(c)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Data Processing</span></b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;
mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'>:</span> Account creation
involves processing of Client’s personal data (or Client’s employee data) as
set out in Schedule C (DPA). Client warrants it has obtained all necessary
consents under PDPO for <span class=SpellE>Sentimento</span> to process such
data.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'>4.3
The <span class=SpellE>Sentimento</span> Seal – Conditional Acceptance</span></b><b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Breaking
the <span class=SpellE>Sentimento</span> Seal by Client (or any person acting
on Client’s behalf) constitutes:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(a)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Irrevocable acceptance</span></b> that Configuration Services are
complete and conforming to the Order <span class=GramE>Form;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(b)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Confirmation</span> </b>that Client Hardware is externally
undamaged as to <span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>patent defects</span> (damage visible upon reasonable inspection<span
class=GramE>);</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(c)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Waiver</span></b> of the right to reject Client Hardware for
visible external damage or incomplete software installation <b><span
style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>save for damage caused by <span class=SpellE>Sentimento’s</span>
negligence during the Configuration Period</span></b> (e.g., scratched screen,
liquid damage during installation<span class=GramE>);</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(d)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Acknowledgment</span> </b>of receipt of all Vertical Modules
selected in the <span class=SpellE>MonoClaw</span> <span class=GramE>website;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(e)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Acceptance</span> </b>of the terms of Schedule B (Vertical Module <span
class=SpellE>Licence</span>) and Schedule C (DPA) (if applicable); and<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(f)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Confirmation</span></b> that Client has reviewed and understood
the “No Remote Control” limitations set out in Schedule B, Section 2.2.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(g)
<b>Non-Extinguishment of Payment Obligation</b>: Breaking the <span
class=SpellE>Sentimento</span> Seal and accepting delivery of the configured
Client Hardware constitutes irrevocable acceptance of the Configuration
Services as complete, but shall not extinguish, diminish, or postpone Client’s
obligation to pay the remaining sixty percent (60%) of the Configuration Fee in
accordance with Clause 12.4(c)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'>4.4
Preservation of Latent Defect Rights</span></b><b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>Breaking
the <span class=SpellE>Sentimento</span> Seal does <b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;
mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'>not</span> </b>prejudice Client’s
rights regarding:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(a)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Latent defects</span></b> in Client Hardware (defects not
discoverable by reasonable inspection at delivery), provided Client notifies
Apple directly within applicable warranty <span class=GramE>periods;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(b)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Damage caused by <span class=SpellE>Sentimento’s</span> negligence</span></b>
during Configuration (evidenced by pre-configuration photos<span class=GramE>);</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(c)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Software functionality defects</span></b> discoverable only after
installation and first use, provided notice is given within 48 hours of seal
breakage.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'>4.5
Apple Warranty Disclosure and Indemnity</span></b><b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(a)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Disclosure:</span></b> Client acknowledges that breaking original
Apple packaging seals to perform Configuration Services may void or limit Apple’s
Limited Warranty for hardware. <span class=SpellE>Sentimento</span> is <span
style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>not</span> an Apple <span class=SpellE>Authorised</span> Service
Provider.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(b)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>No Hardware Warranty</span></b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;
mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'>:</span> <span class=SpellE>Sentimento</span>
provides no warranty regarding Apple hardware condition, which remains subject
solely to Apple’s Limited Warranty and the Sale of Goods Ordinance (Cap. 26) as
between Client and Apple.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(c)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Indemnity</span></b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;
mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'>:</span> Client shall indemnify
<span class=SpellE>Sentimento</span> against any loss of Apple warranty
benefits, repair coverage, or support entitlements arising from <span
class=SpellE>Sentimento’s</span> configuration work, including costs of repairs
that would have been covered by Apple but for warranty voidance.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'>4.6
Gatekeeper Protocol for Tier 1 Tools</span></b><b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span class=SpellE><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman",serif'>Sentimento</span></span><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>
shall <b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>not</span> </b>install any Tier 1 Tools (Legal, Medical/Dental,
Accounting, or Immigration Modules) unless Client has first satisfied the
following verification requirements:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(a)
<b><span style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>Professional Status Documentation</span></b><span
style='border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;
padding:0in'>:</span> Client shall provide, to their <b>Dashboard</b> on <span
class=SpellE>MonoClaw’s</span> website, certified true copies of:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;
