</span>iv.<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:.4pt'>Injunctive
Relief</span></b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:
.4pt'>: Seek urgent interim injunctive relief from the Hong Kong courts to
prevent further disclosure or misuse of the address.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>(e) <b>Survival</b><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>The obligations under this Clause 12.5 survive termination
of this Agreement for a period of <b>five (5) years</b>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:center;
line-height:110%'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>CLAUSE 13: DELIVERY TIMELINE, DELAY REMEDIES AND FORCE
MAJEURE<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>13.1 Delivery Window<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>(a) <span class=SpellE>Sentimento</span> shall use
commercially reasonable <span class=SpellE>endeavours</span> to complete
Configuration Services and dispatch the configured Client Hardware to Client
within <b>seven (7) to fourteen (14) Business Days </b>following the date of <span
class=SpellE>Sentimento’s</span> actual receipt of the Client Hardware from
Apple or its <span class=SpellE>authorised</span> carrier (“Receipt Date”).<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>(b) The Receipt Date shall be recorded on the Client’s
dashboard accessible via </span><a href="http://www.monoclaw.app"><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:.4pt'>www.monoclaw.app</span></a><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;letter-spacing:.4pt'> and notified
to Client by email within <b>twenty-four (24) hours</b> of physical receipt.
The dashboard shall display an Estimated Delivery Date calculated as the
Receipt Date plus <b>ten (10) Business Days</b> (being the midpoint of the
contractual window).<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>13.2 Permitted Delay Buffer<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>Notwithstanding Clause 13.1, <span class=SpellE>Sentimento</span>
shall be entitled to a <b>seven (7) Business Day</b> buffer period (“Permitted
Buffer”) without penalty, provided that the delay is caused by one or more of
the following circumstances and <span class=SpellE>Sentimento</span> notifies
Client via the Dashboard within <b>forty-eight (48) hours </b>of becoming aware
of the delay:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>(a) Technical incompatibility between Client Hardware
specifications and selected Local Models requiring unscheduled quantization,
optimization, or testing beyond standard <span class=GramE>workflow;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>(b) Delayed receipt of complete Gatekeeper Protocol
documentation (Clause 4.6) or professional insurance certificates from Client
for Tier 1 Tool <span class=GramE>installation;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>(c) Discovery of latent hardware defects during diagnostic
testing requiring consultation with Client or return to Apple for warranty <span
class=GramE>replacement;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>(d) Temporary unavailability of specific model weights
from Upstream Licensors due to repository outages, geographic IP blocking, or <span
class=SpellE>licence</span> server <span class=GramE>failures;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>(e) Compliance with mandatory public health orders,
workplace safety protocols, or building management restrictions affecting <span
class=SpellE>Sentimento’s</span> configuration <span class=GramE>facility;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>(f) Order volume exceeding <span class=SpellE>Sentimento’s</span>
stated processing capacity for the relevant calendar month (provided <span
class=SpellE>Sentimento</span> publishes current capacity on its website<span
class=GramE>);</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>(g) Client-requested modifications to the Order Form after
Receipt Date; or<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>(h) Any other operational constraint beyond <span
class=SpellE>Sentimento’s</span> reasonable control that does not rise to the
level of Force Majeure.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>13.3 Delay Compensation and Liquidated Damages<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>If delivery occurs after the expiry of the fourteen (14)
Business Day window specified in Clause 13.1, Client shall be entitled to the
following deductions from the Configuration Fee as liquidated damages (not
penalties):<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>(a) Minor Delay (within Permitted Buffer): If delivery
occurs between the 15th and 21st Business Day after the Receipt Date
(inclusive), <span class=SpellE>Sentimento</span> shall apply a discount of
five percent (5%) to ten percent (10%) of the Configuration Fee, the exact
percentage to be determined by <span class=SpellE>Sentimento</span> in good
faith based on the length of delay and mitigating factors;<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>(b) Significant Delay (beyond Permitted Buffer): If
delivery occurs after the 21st Business Day after the Receipt Date, Client
shall be entitled to a discount of twenty-five percent (25%) of the
Configuration Fee.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>(c) Maximum Liability: The aggregate liability of <span
class=SpellE>Sentimento</span> for delay under this Clause 13.3 shall not
exceed twenty-five percent (25%) of the Configuration Fee, and <span
class=SpellE>Sentimento</span> shall have no liability for delays caused by
Force Majeure (Clause 13.4) or Client’s acts/omissions.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>13.4 Force Majeure<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
letter-spacing:.4pt'>(a) Definition: Neither party shall be liable for any
failure or delay in performing its obligations under this Agreement (including
the delivery timelines in Clause 13.1) where such failure or delay arises from
circumstances outside the affected party’s reasonable control, including but
not limited to:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;
margin-bottom:4.0pt;margin-left:28.35pt;mso-add-space:auto;text-align:justify;
text-justify:inter-ideograph;text-indent:-28.35pt;mso-text-indent-alt:-7.05pt;
line-height:110%;mso-list:l6 level1 lfo37'><![if !supportLists]><span
