border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'>3.1
Legal Profession Warranty</span></b><b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>If
any Legal Module is selected, Client warrants that:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(a)
Client is a solicitor admitted under the Legal Practitioners Ordinance (Cap.
159), a registered foreign lawyer under Part IXA of Cap. 159, or a
paralegal/legal clerk working under the direct supervision of such solicitor
who holds a current <span class=SpellE>practising</span> <span class=GramE>certificate;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(b)
Client maintains valid <span class=SpellE>practising</span> certificates and
professional indemnity insurance as required by the Hong Kong Law Society or
Solicitors’ Indemnity Fund (minimum coverage HKD $1,000,000 or as prescribed<span
class=GramE>);</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(c)
Use of Legal Modules constitutes administrative support only and does not
constitute the provision of legal advice to third parties without solicitor <span
class=GramE>supervision;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif'>(d)
Client shall not use Legal Modules to provide legal services to the public
unless through a law firm properly registered under Cap. 159.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:4.0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:
inter-ideograph;line-height:110%'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

